
[1]confinement

   CONFI'NEMENT, n.

   1. Restraint within limits; imprisonment; any restraint of liberty by
   force or other obstacle or necessity; as the confinement of a debtor or
   criminal to a prison, or of troops to a besieged town.

   2. Voluntary restraint; seclusion; as the confinement of a man to his
   house, or to his studies.

   3. Voluntary restraint in action or practice; as confinement to a
   particular diet.

   4. Restraint from going abroad by sickness, particularly by
   child-birth.
